# Amicus Curiae Brief

Drafts an appellate amicus curiae brief in compliance with applicable procedural rules and court requirements.

## Prerequisites

1. Identify forum and filing stage (cert-stage or merits-stage).
2. Confirm docket number and filing deadlines.
3. Obtain copies of party briefs for reference.
4. Compile relevant citations from the record.
5. Establish amicus identity, interest, and relationship to parties.
6. Secure necessary consent or court leave for filing.
7. Prepare required disclosures under applicable rules.
8. Confirm authorship, funding, and source disclosures.
9. Review formatting requirements including cover color and copy counts.
10. Gather sources for legislative facts and supporting authorities.

## Output Structure / Process

**Intake Checklist**

| Item                      | Purpose                                     | Required? |
|---------------------------|---------------------------------------------|-----------|
| Forum and Stage           | Determine applicable rules and deadlines    | Yes       |
| Docket Number             | Identifies case                              | Yes       |
| Deadlines                 | Ensure timely filing                         | Yes       |
| Party Briefs              | Reference for arguments                       | Yes       |
| Record Citations          | Support adjudicative facts                    | Yes       |
| Amicus Identity & Interest| Establish standing and disclose relationship | Yes       |
| Consent or Leave          | Obtain permission to file                     | Yes       |
| Disclosures               | Meet disclosure and funding obligations      | Yes       |
| Authorship & Funding      | Transparency of brief creation                | Yes       |
| Formatting Requirements   | Comply with local and court-specific rules   | Yes       |

**Compliance Map**

| Rule Set                 | Deadline               | Word/Page Limit | Disclosures                | Certificates          | Copies/Formatting   | Cover Color         | Local Rules [VERIFY]       |
|--------------------------|------------------------|-----------------|----------------------------|-----------------------|---------------------|---------------------|----------------------------|
| FRAP 29 / FRAP 32        | Per court schedule     | See respective rules | Rule 29 disclosures         | Service certificates  | Number of copies    | Green (Supreme Court) | State/federal variations    |
| Supreme Court Rule 37    | Per cert/merits stage  | See Rule 37 limits | Rule 37 disclosures          | Certificates of service| Formatting specifics| Green cover           | Specific state rules        |

### Thesis Selection

- Identify central argument supporting amicus interest.
- Avoid duplicating party arguments.
- Focus on unique perspective or broader policy implications.

### Record / Fact Handling

| Fact Category          | Citation Type          | Notes                          |
|-----------------------|-----------------------|--------------------------------|
| Adjudicative Facts     | Record citations      | Use for established facts       |
| Legislative Facts      | Authoritative sources  | Cite statutes, regulations      |
| Unverified Claims      | Mark [VERIFY]          | Use caution or confirmation     |

### Brief Outline Template

```markdown
Cover Page  
[Case Caption]  
[Amicus Identifying Information]  

Table of Contents  

Table of Authorities  

Statement of Interest  

Disclosures under FRAP 29 / Rule 37  

Summary of Argument  

Argument  
I. [First Argument Heading]  
   [Develop argument with citations]  
II. [Second Argument Heading]  
   [Develop argument with citations]  

Conclusion  

Certificates of Service and Compliance  
[VERIFY]
```

### Argument Structure Checklist

- [ ] Clear thesis statement
- [ ] Logical organization with headings
- [ ] Use cited authority for support
- [ ] Avoid new issues not raised in parties’ briefs
- [ ] Address consent or leave requirements properly

### Certificate Templates

```markdown
Certificate of Service  
I certify that on [Date], a true and correct copy of this brief was served on [Counsel/Parties] by [Method].  
[VERIFY]  

Certificate of Compliance  
This brief complies with FRAP [29/32] and Supreme Court Rule 37 due to [word count/formatting].  
[VERIFY]  
```

### Quality Control Checklist

- [ ] Verify citations and include [VERIFY] where uncertain
- [ ] Confirm adherence to formatting and cover color
- [ ] Check for required disclosures and consents
- [ ] Ensure no duplication of party arguments
- [ ] Review for compliance with applicable rules and deadlines
- [ ] Confirm Supreme Court Bar membership if needed
- [ ] Ensure record citations for adjudicative facts
- [ ] Use legislative facts supported by sources
- [ ] Maintain professional tone without press-release style
- [ ] Attorney review completed before filing

## Guidelines

- Do not duplicate arguments made by parties.
- Do not raise new issues unless explicitly permitted.
- Label all uncertain citations with [VERIFY].
- Use record citations exclusively for adjudicative facts.
- Use legislative facts only when supported by authoritative sources.
- Avoid press-release or promotional tone.
- Confirm Supreme Court Bar membership if filing there.
- Rules vary by jurisdiction; always obtain and review the current text.
- Attorney review is required before final submission.
- Comply with Model Rules of Professional Conduct as ethical guidance.

